-- Greece says sold 4.75 pct coupon, 5-yr bond, mostly to foreigners
-- 
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 07:11AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, April 10 (Reuters) - Greece confirmed on Thursday it sold 3 billion euros ($4.15 billion) worth of 5-year bonds at an annual coupon of 4.75 percent.

"Demand for the bonds was very strong. Participation of foreign institutional investors is expected to approach 90 percent," the finance ministry said in a statement.